Rating: 4
I made this for a birthday dinner along with a traditional family cheesecake. WOW! We all loved it. It's light and delicious. Truly a world-class dessert. A few changes: I halved the sugar for the main part of the cheesecake. I did not reduce the sugar for the sour creme part. Delicious! I also substituted blueberries for strawberries. Blueberries and raspberries make for a wonderful combination. LOVE this recipe and will make it again and again. This is a new family classic.

Rating: 4
This cheesecake was very easy to make. I actually added some berries to the mixer after I folded the egg whites into the cream cheese. I also added some lemon juice to the sour cream mixture. The cake came out great. The only issue I ran into was that I had to cook my cake about 15 minutes longer than the recipe called for. will make again, and try other creative "stir ins" but a really great basic recipe.

Rating: 4
I am NOT a dessert maker but as I was tasked with bringing a dessert for our Family Xmas dinner. This was a real winner and easy-peasy! I particularly enjoyed how light tasting it was. I decorated the top with concentric rows of raspberries only and it looked lovely.

Rating: 4
it was loved (and yes, request for the recipe followed). I made a gingersnap crust (same proportions but with gingersnaps and some ground ginger and crystallized ginger if you have some on hand) and also added lime to the mix, about 1 1/2 tsp zest and the juice of 1 lime. I also added the yolks to the batter because I didn't want to waste them and it also was great, gave it a nice color. very good stuff. I love the whipped egg whites.

