Rating: 2
I was disappointed with this recipe for two reasons. When made a day in advance, the crust had softened to the point of being too soggy for my taste. Second, while the light texture of the filling was appealing, I felt its taste needed to be sparked up with a berry sauce, and not just unadorned fresh berries. I will try another recipe next time.

Rating: 4
Delectable! After pouring in half the batter, I sprinkled 1 cup berries on top, then finished with the rest of the batter. After baking and refrigerating, I garnished with more raspberries. I really like the texture that folding the egg whites in created. This cake is not too sweet and just the right consistency.

